<div class="container">
  <section class="rules-combined">
    <div class="quiz-divider" style="margin:0 0 16px"><span>⚡ Regeln auf einen Blick</span></div>
    <div class="rc-grid">

      <!-- 1 AUSSAGESATZ -->
      <div class="rc-card c-green">
        <div class="rc-card-topbar"></div>
        <div class="rc-card-num">1</div>
        <div class="rc-card-body">
          <div class="rc-card-label">✅ Aussagesatz</div>
          <div class="rc-formula">
            <span class="fc fc-subj">Subjekt</span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-do">am/is/are</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-do">going to</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-verb">Verb (Grundform)</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="rc-rule"><b>Form von to be</b> richtet sich nach dem Subjekt:<br>I → <b>am</b><br>you → <b>are</b><br>he → <b>is</b><br>she → <b>is</b><br>it → <b>is</b><br>we → <b>are</b><br>you → <b>are</b><br>they → <b>are</b><br>Verb bleibt in der Grundform – kein -s, kein -ing!</div>
          <div class="rc-examples-new">
            <span class="hl-subj">I</span> <span class="hl-do">am going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">visit</span> my grandma.<br>
            <span class="hl-subj">She</span> <span class="hl-do">is going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">play</span> tennis.<br>
            <span class="hl-subj">They</span> <span class="hl-do">are going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">watch</span> a film.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 2 VERNEINUNG -->
      <div class="rc-card c-red">
        <div class="rc-card-topbar"></div>
        <div class="rc-card-num">2</div>
        <div class="rc-card-body">
          <div class="rc-card-label">❌ Verneinung</div>
          <div class="rc-formula">
            <span class="fc fc-subj">Subjekt</span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-do">am/is/are</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-neg">not</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-do">going to</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-verb">Verb</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="rc-rule"><b>not</b> kommt direkt nach am/is/are.<br>Kurzformen: <b>isn't · aren't</b> (aber <b>I am not</b> oder <b>I'm not</b>, niemals „amn't“)</div>
          <div class="rc-examples-new">
            <span class="hl-subj">He</span> <span class="hl-do">is</span> <span class="hl-neg">not</span> <span class="hl-do">going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">come</span>.<br>
            <span class="hl-subj">We</span> <span class="hl-neg">aren't</span> <span class="hl-do">going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">go</span> swimming.<br>
            <span class="hl-subj">I</span> <span class="hl-neg">am not</span> <span class="hl-do">going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">help</span>.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 3 JA/NEIN-FRAGE -->
      <div class="rc-card c-blue">
        <div class="rc-card-topbar"></div>
        <div class="rc-card-num">3</div>
        <div class="rc-card-body">
          <div class="rc-card-label">❓ Ja/Nein-Frage</div>
          <div class="rc-formula">
            <span class="fc fc-do">Am/Is/Are</span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-subj">Subjekt</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-do">going to</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-verb">Verb</span></span><span class="fc-punct">?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rc-rule"><b>am/is/are</b> rutscht ganz nach vorne.<br><span style="font-size:12px;">💬 Short Answer: <b>Yes, I am.</b> · <b>No, she isn't.</b> · <b>Yes, they are.</b></span></div>
          <div class="rc-examples-new">
            <span class="hl-do">Is</span> <span class="hl-subj">she</span> <span class="hl-do">going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">come</span>? – <b>Yes, she <span class="hl-do">is</span>.</b><br>
            <span class="hl-do">Are</span> <span class="hl-subj">they</span> <span class="hl-do">going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">play</span>? – <b>No, they <span class="hl-neg">aren't</span>.</b>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 4 W-FRAGE -->
      <div class="rc-card c-indigo">
        <div class="rc-card-topbar"></div>
        <div class="rc-card-num">4</div>
        <div class="rc-card-body">
          <div class="rc-card-label">🔵 W-Frage</div>
          <div class="rc-formula">
            <span class="fc fc-wh">W-Wort</span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-do">am/is/are</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-subj">Subjekt</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-do">going to</span></span><span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">+</span><span class="fc fc-verb">Verb</span></span><span class="fc-punct">?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rc-rule"><b>What · Where · When · Who · Why · How</b> – immer ganz vorne!<br>Dann am/is/are, dann Subjekt.</div>
          <div class="rc-examples-new">
            <span class="hl-wh">Where</span> <span class="hl-do">are</span> <span class="hl-subj">you</span> <span class="hl-do">going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">spend</span> the holidays?<br>
            <span class="hl-wh">What</span> <span class="hl-do">is</span> <span class="hl-subj">she</span> <span class="hl-do">going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">do</span> tomorrow?
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 5 WANN BENUTZE ICH ES -->
      <div class="rc-card c-amber">
        <div class="rc-card-topbar"></div>
        <div class="rc-card-num">5</div>
        <div class="rc-card-body">
          <div class="rc-card-label">⏱ Wann benutze ich es?</div>
          <div class="rc-formula" style="flex-wrap:wrap;gap:5px 4px">
            <span class="fc fc-do" style="font-size:10px">geplante Pläne</span>
            <span class="fc-pair"><span class="fc-plus">·</span><span class="fc fc-verb" style="font-size:10px">Vorhersage mit Beweis</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="rc-rule">Das Going to Future benutzt man bei:<br>• <b>geplanten Handlungen</b> (vorher entschieden)<br>• <b>Vorhersagen mit sichtbaren Anzeichen</b><br><span style="font-size:12px;color:#9a7050;">⚠️ Unterschied zu will: going to = vorher geplant · will = spontan beim Reden entschieden</span></div>
          <div class="rc-examples-new">
            I <span class="hl-do">am going to</span> <span class="hl-verb">visit</span> Paris next week. <span style="font-size:11px;color:#9a7050">(Plan)</span><br>
